				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514779"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[1]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>Last night, my friend starting sending me tells of a GM event going on in Everfrost.  He kept telling me that the tower that was normally empty was on a timer that would spawn a mad spectre, 2 skellies, and 2 werebats. </p>
  <p>  They would each spawn about 3 times before you would have to wait for the next timer time to start it over again.  It was I, Smallcat Bloodclaws a most faithful server in the ranks of the Legions of Ragnarok, and my good ranger friend, Tanbil Bladeslinger, who held the tower and vanquished the undead fiends. </p>
  <p>  The only loot the enemies dropped was a headpiece for clr/dru/shm and a bracelet for enc/nec/wiz/mag, and some gold.  Not to mention the rune of ultimate evil.  It was fun and I enjoyed it thoroughly.</p>
  <p>Smallcat Bloodclaws <Legions of Ragnarok><br>
  dwarven warrior in his 20th year of battle</p>
