				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="21">GM events on XEV</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:zackman2@hotmail.com">Zurkanaz</b></a>
				[11/2/2001-6:18:54 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514710"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>In the past two days, there have been GM events in the Xev server in the West Commandlands. The sky turns red, and you hear the consistant howling of werewolves. Lesser, Greater, Minor, and regular Werewolves were seen. </p>
  <p> They drop class specific, no-drop lore magical items. SK only rings and gloves, Enchanter only Cloak and earing, Warrior only earing, and many more. There was supposedly 2 specific items per class. These items have outrageous stats and decay if left on a corpse. </p>
  <p> There was also the Lord Werewolf. When killed, the GM event ends, with a universal message something like this: "The lord cries out, you have conquered me, but I shall return someday" and then "The ground is littered with corpses, and the werewolves, with full stomaches, stop their howling and slowing leave." </p>
  <p>This event has orrcured on Thurday and Friday, from the times of: 4-5PM EA, 7-8PM EA. These were the times they started, and it ends when the Lord is killied. Next time you in West Commandlands area, check it out. But beware, the werewolves and high levels, and when I wnt there, the characters there were all lvl 30 and up.<br>
  </p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
