				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="24">GM Events on Luclin!</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:elisaren@loveable.com">Elisaren</b></a>
				[11/1/2001-9:42:54 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514315"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[10]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>There were a Number of GM events on Luclin.  Including East Karana, Qeynos Hills, West Commonlands, and the Mountains of Rathe.&nbsp;<br>
  <br>
  In Qeynos Hills the zone was full of various Skeletons.  Skeletal Soldiers, Corprorals, Footmen, and Spearmen.  Also Warboned Skellies that were the size of the Giant Skellies normally in Mountains of Rathe.  It went on all night, and the skellies all dropped rusty weapons and bone chips.  The Warboned Skellies sometimes had an Opal (15pp to merchant).  I heard when it started they all had better loot, but I didn't get there right away.<br>
  <br>
  In the Mountains of Rathe there were a number of mobs running around, they looked like black mares, specters, gargoyles, and bone dragons.  There was a named bone dragon called the Blood Reaver that had Dragon Fear and a 500DD+ AoE spell.  When killed he dropped an Ax for SK's, a warrior, and a caster isle.  He would respawn every so often.  All the mobs had random, no-drop, class specific loot on them.  (Lore of course)  Including an earing:<br>
  <br>
  Hollowed Pixy Rib Earing<br>
  AC 1 WIS+4 HP+20 Mana+20<br>
  CLR/DRU/SHM<br>
  Lore, Magic, No-drop<br>
  <br>
  And a wizzy cloak that had stats including AC9 and INT+7.  In addition to some saves.<br>
  <br>
  There were at least 2 items that dropped for each class/class-type and when a mob dropped these items they dropped two of such lore and no-drop items.<br>
  <br>
  In the West Commonlands there were Werewolves running about, I was unable to attend this one, but they were apparently low level.<br>
  <br>
  In East Karana there was also undead about, but I was also unable to attend this GM event.<br>
  <br>
  It was all fun, and I have to say an on-going GM event was pretty cool.  Even if GM's didn't play a big part in them the whole time.  I heard the Blood Reaver was played by a GM the first time.  But I can't confirm this.<br>
  <br>
  Happy Holloween!<br>
  <br>
  Elisaren Silverymoon<br>
  High Elf Cleric of Tunare, Luclin<br>
  &lt;Knights of Velious></p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
