				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="26">Vazaelle under siege</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:svpaladin@netzero.net">Julin</b></a>
				[11/1/2001-7:25:11 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514269"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[0]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>The Vazaelle server has had a lot of wierd happenings in the past 24 hours.<br>
  <br>
  Twice in the eyes of this mage West Commons was afflicted with a strange happening.  The skies turned orange, and the region was swamped with werewolves of all sizes.  These wolves carried fine items, all of which were the property of the claimant, and very specific in the user allowed.<br>
  <br>
  Late on the night of all hollow's eve, a Deacon raised a sunken ship out of the deep waters in the Ocean of Tears, and a brave band had travelled on the ship to Spectre Island, where they encountered the crew of that ship, which, from reports, was neither dead nor undead.  At the Deacon's request, these intrepid adventurers slain the crew, alas, the captain of the ship had escaped that night.  This information came to me via the calls of those who adventured on this quest, while I held outpost on Aviak Isle.<br>
  <br>
  The last thing this mage has seen is a mass of undead gathering in Kithicor forest, for what looked like an assault on something.  They had gathered at the Queynos directional marker, marking the intersection where if you went north, you'd go to Riverdale / Misty Thicket.  This mage did not watch where they were planning to go, ill prepared to stave off the undead, I returned to the commons in order to raise the alarm.</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
