				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="27">Halloween in Rathe Mountains on Ayonae Ro</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:truk_truespirit@hotmail.com">Truk Truespirit</b></a>
				[11/1/2001-2:31:27 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514199"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[8]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>Hail and well met friends,<br>
  <br>
  Truk Truespirit of Fated Unity here. I was adventuring in South Karana today when a guildmate told us of an event taking place in Rathe Mountains. The undead were taking over the zone!! Myself and others from my guild immediately headed to the zone to help. </p>
  <p> Once arriving, we were amazed by the sight of the undead; Everything from huge skeleton drakes to spectres and undead horses. There were many people in the zone battling the numerous undead. My guildmates and I headed to HG hill and I was feared by a large undead drake and subsequently died after being hit for 500 damage twice. I enjoyed the event whole heartedly though, in fact it was the most fun I've had in game. </p>
  <p> Alot of loot was recieved and shared by everyone. I personally recieved an earring with stats ac+1, +4wisdom, +20hp, +20mana and a 2hb 13damage,    40delay +5sv disease, +5sv magic. The thing that I really noticed is that people of our server were calling out the loot so as to share with everyone. Way to go Ayonae Ro!!</p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
