				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="28">GM Event on Tunare Server -</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Kubax Gurtholfin</b></a>
				[11/1/2001-12:46:28 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=514185"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>Hail all, Wanderers of Norrath !<br>
  <br>
  Let me tell you what happened yesterday, so it may not be forgotten soon...<br>
  <br>
  Yesterday, as i awoke in the ever-busy and buzzing Greater Faydark, i received word that something was happening to me beautiful home of Everfrost. I immediately gated back home....only to find it too warm in the whole of Everfrost ! Something - or someone - seemed to have influenced the weather ! As i shouted what was going on, i received Battle Crys and shouts about the Living Dead and Werewolves haunting our lands ! I prayed to The Tribunal to send me a Frenzied Spirit to aid me, and after some preparation, me trusty Companion and me went on to rid our Land of the Invaders. Many Werewolves i encountered, and uncommon strong Skeletons were wandering around as well - they showed no fear and even dared to attack me...they all didnt last long. </p>
  <p> After a while, and talking to numerous Barbarian Sisters and Brothers and other friends o´ mine, a Barbarian named Shamus seemed to know where these beasts came from. I received a Diary from Shamus, the one who belonged to the Leader of the Beasts, a evil Sorceress. The diary reveiled that she was trying to become like the Gods, through three special Runes and a foul Ceremonie were said to make her invincible. Yet there was hope, she also wrote down about what seemed to be her Arch-Enemy who was named MORDAG. I found this man shortly after - he was a Barbarian like me...and he told me more about the danger that was threatening Everfrost and the whole of Norrath. He told me to bring him the 3 Runes so that the Evil Sorceress Plans could be stopped. He didnt know where to find them, but through the diary i knew there were 3 Camps of the Undead. The most powerful servants of Evil, the Mad Spectres, guarded the Rune of Ultimate Evil (though it was mentioned in the diary as Rune of Ultimate Chaos), the Rune of Endless Life and the Rune of Endless Mana. They also were in the possession of other unique items - i found meself a PEGASUS FEATHERED HEADDRESS, a magical and unique item that not only granted me WIS+4, but also increased my MANA+4 and my SV DISEASE+4, without ANY weight.....</p>
  <p><br>
  The Servants of the Evil Sorceress were no match - i received all 3 Runes and went back to Mordag. As i gave them to him, he payed me some Gold and Platinum pieces as reward. Just as we were about to go to Halas to destroy the Runes so that they NEVER might fall into the wrong hands - the Evil Sorceress materialized, cursing and attacking me instantly ! I did what i had to do...and moments later, her accursed form was lying before me, bleeding to death. With her dying breath, she muttered some more curses and that she will be back one day....but i didnt pay attention, for the Snow Leopards were closing in on her - and they seemed hungry....<br>
  <br>
  /ooc Many thanks to all GM who thought of those wonderful Events and such throughout Norrath ! Keep up the good work ! :)<br>
  <br>
  <br>
  Kubax Gurtholfin, the "Hammer of Death"<br>
  Order of Mjolnir<br>
  Tunare Server<br>
  </p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		

