				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="30">GM event on Erollisi Marr</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:">Chiatae Li'Kung</b></a>
				[10/31/2001-9:48:40 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=513897"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[4]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>A Paebla rat in Dragon Necropolis named Prophet Jandari wanted to set his people free from the dragons.  He required a few items so that he could fashion a weapon to slay the dragons.<br>
  <br>
  The Prophet sent us to various zones throughout Norrath, collecting items that he would use to fashion a weapon.<br>
  <br>
  We had to fight various creatures in each zone, but the final battle took place in Dragon Necropolis.  We had to slay a dragon named Jaren'Zar.  However, it was not one dragon, but four different versions of him!<br>
  <br>
  Jaren'Zar, Jaren'Zar's skin, Jaren'Zar's bones and finally Jaren'Zar's shade!  Intense battles were fought with many falling to the deaths.  We ressed and continued to fight until each dragon fell at our feet, permanently "Afflicted".  During the final battle with the "Shade", the Prophet stepped into melee range with his weapon that he fashioned and helped us slay the final dragon.<br>
  <br>
  The Prophet rewarded not only me, but others in our guild that participated as well!<br>
  <br>
  Chiatae - Cowl of Mortality<br>
  Breus - Fungi Tunic<br>
  Ojuillean - Tink Bag<br>
  Barbasol - Sarnak Battle Shield<br>
  Assilem - Horn of Hsaagra<br>
  Sharasali - Lodizal Shell Shield<br>
  <br>
  Guild info and updates:<br>
  www.afflictionguild.com<br>
  <br>
  Screenshots of the event: <a href="http://www.afflictionguild.com/imagegallery.php?charactername=Chiatae">http://www.afflictionguild.com/imagegallery.php?charactername=Chiatae</a><br>
  <br>
  This was an extremely fun event!  Would like to thank the GM's of Emarr for running this, we all had a great time!<br>
  <br>
  <br>
  </p>
</blockquote></font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
