				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="33">Crushbone Scavenger Hunt on Drinal</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:meienea@hotmail.com">Meienea Cloudstalker</b></a>
				[10/31/2001-5:59:20 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=513820"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[1]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>Greetings denizens of Drinal.  On Saturday November 3 at 6:00PM EST the Throne of Drinal will be hosting a scavenger hunt in Crushbone. </p>
  <p>  We will also be providing buffing, healing and trainbreaking for all in need of such services and a wide arrange of refreshments.  The scavenger hunt itself is open to all characters between levels 7 and 15 and multiple prizes will be given away.  Hope to see you there.</p>
</blockquote>
</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
				<a href="/NewsAdmin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=513816">										
				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="34">GM event on Xegony</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:windowgod@hotmail.com">Darco</b></a>
				[10/31/2001-5:48:35 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=513816"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[5]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>A group of Judgment was sitting in GFay having drinks and chatting when a young fellow ran through Kelethin shouting that Dagnor's Cauldron was under attack. Judgment sprang into action and rushed to Dagnor's Cauldron. </p>
  <p> We were puzzled by the quietness, and were about to return to GFay to finish our drinks. As we were leaving we heard screams of death coming from the Estate of Unrest. We rushed to be of service. As we entered we found a group of GM controlled Ogres had taken control of the Estate of Unrest. </p>
  <p> The foul Ogres were screaming that we didn't belong there and immediately began to attack us. Zastik summoned and undead servant and quickly went to work. Jutak and Indiana held the attackers at bay. Heelur blasted hard and fast at the Ogres. </p>
  <p> The Ogres had left a field of blood for the young, but they were no match for the Judgment crew. The Judges quickly passed sentence on the Ogres, and the sentence was death. We searched their bodies to get an idea of who they were. They had little on them, and nothing of real interest. He headed back to GFay leaving a stain of blood on the ground. The Ogres were nothing but a memory....<br>
  </p>
</blockquote>
</font></p><p>&nbsp;</p>
		
				<a href="/NewsAdmin.asp?mode=edit&amp;id=513754">										
				<img BORDER="0" ALT="Edit/Delete" src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif"></a>
		
				<font face="verdana" size="3"><a name="35">Klicta`Kar</a></font><br>
				<font face="verdana" size="2">
				<b><a href="mailto:vze2556w@verizon.net">Dermorat Trainpuller</b></a>
				[10/31/2001-3:35:19 AM]</font>
				&nbsp;<a href="Comments.asp?ID=513754"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Comments[3]</font></a><p>
				<font face="verdana" size="2"><blockquote>
  <p>At the Turn of Midnight and the Begining of All Hallows Eve, we had a grand GM event on the Povar server!<br>
  <br>
  Messages went out in the Lake of Ill Omen<br>
  "Ripples race along the water."<br>
  "The water splashes you look closely at the water. You see a strange shadow in the lake."<br>
  <br>
  A wurm named Klicta`Kar emerged from the lake of Ill Omen. People from all over flocked in to help kill the beast. We chased it from the mouth of the stream at the FV zone to the front door of the Sarnak Fort and half way back again before we were able to take the great beast down. It was casting a mass fear spell that would send people running away in waves with the feared [LD] tag next to there name. Once the beast was killed nobody would tell what they looted from it. However one of my guild mates in (Fellowship Circle) was lucky enough to get second loot and pulled off from it a Werewolf Skin Cloak (AC5  Str3 Sta3)<br>
  <br>
  Following are several pictures of the event</p>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="http://www.everlore.com/ShowScreenShot.asp?ID=513757"><font face="Verdana" size="2">Attached
